    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Nvim Lua stdlib (or the editor stdlib--doesn't matter which, really) should have various path utilities, e.g. \r\n\r\n- mimic python's `commonpath()` function.  https://docs.python.org/3/library/os.path.html#os.path.commonpath\r\n  - useful for comparing ancestor/descendant relationships. https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lsp/pull/61#discussion_r355251268\r\n- path `join()` function (how does Vim not have this already?!)\r\n\r\n",
